		<iframe width="420" height="315" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/rtXbi5X88wU" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
	</div>

	<br />

	Now, check out this version of Tweezer from Phish's 2013 Fall Tour, which clocked in at just under 18 minutes:<br /><br />
	
	<div class="video-wrapper">
		<iframe width="560" height="315" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/rg77L7e9EQY" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
	</div>

	<br />

	(Tweezer, in fact, is what's known as a "jam vehicle", a song particularly known to fuel long and cohesive jams -- more on this later.)<br /><br />

	<span class="phish-highlight">The band does not write setlists for shows.</span> The band does, however, have a master list of more than two hundred songs that they know and are able to play at any given time. <br /><br />

	Every song placement within the scope of a show is a call made on the spot, a <span class="phish-highlight">complete audible</span>. Every performance is completely unique, featuring different songs, as well as different extended improvisations contained within each of these different songs.<br /><br />

	<div class="phish-pictures">
